The paper deals with an algorithmic problem in numerical linear algebra, specifically the Column Subset Selection Problem (CSSP). This problem is related to matrix factorization and has applications in data analysis and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves probability theory and information theory, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents theoretical bounds on the performance of the algorithm, which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
